<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - DISASSEMBLE - REMOTE CONTROL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301603">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301603" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301603" filename="../figg13/G1301603.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Remote Control Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and lockwashers and separate the remote control from the shifter housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the setscrew from the universal joint assembly and pull the universal joint from the
                rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts and lockwashers that hold the end cover and gasket in place.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the setscrew from the U-joint shift rod finger and tap the rod through the cross
                holes in the housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the finger from the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the setscrew from the inner shift finger.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the rod and bracket assembly from the inner shift finger. Be careful not to lose the
                key from the rod or shift finger.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the seals from the housing cross holes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the shift fingers for excessive wear. Check all bores and rods for excessive wear or
                scuffing. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all parts thoroughly and apply a light coat of grease to all pivot points prior to
                reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
